# Optimizely Opal & CMP – Documentation and Best Practices

When planning or editing workflow/agent JSON or prompts for this project, consult the following docs and follow their patterns.

## Official Optimizely documentation (reference)

- **System tools overview:** https://support.optimizely.com/hc/en-us/articles/39340107628429-System-tools-overview  
- **System tools for Campaign:** https://support.optimizely.com/hc/en-us/articles/42021008282765-System-tools-for-Campaign  
- **System tools for CMP:** https://support.optimizely.com/hc/en-us/articles/39681551954957-System-tools-for-Content-Marketing-Platform-CMP  

Check these for up-to-date tool parameters, when to use each tool, and example prompts.

## Local Opal examples

- **Repo:** `docs/opal-agent-examples/` (README and specialized agents).
- **Prompt structure reference:** `docs/opal-agent-examples/specialized-agents/bank-content-compliance.json` – use **Goal → Guardrails (must follow) → Input → Process → Output**.
- **Conventions:** Call-once per tool per path; send_email exactly once per path then return.

## Best practices to enforce

1. **Prompt structure:** Role/Goal, Guardrails (must follow), Input, Process (numbered steps), Output (exact JSON shape). No free-form returns.
2. **Tool usage:** One call per path per tool where specified. **send_email:** call exactly once per execution path (success or failure), then return immediately; do not call again or re-enter earlier steps.
3. **Conditions:** Use **equals** (not contains) for workflow routing fields (e.g. event_type, proceed_status, has_supporting_activity). "Contains" can mis-match (e.g. "Not Accepted" containing "Accepted").
4. **Schema:** Required fields and enums in agent output must match what the workflow evaluator and next step expect. Document or add any pass-through fields (e.g. task_urls, has_supporting_activity).

